Headings always use sentence-case (not title-case), excluding H1 page headings which are all-caps.

```jsx
<div>
  <h4 className="typography-body-10 text-text-muted mb-3">For example:</h4>
  <p className="typography-body-10 mb-2 ml-4">
    <span className="text-text-success font-bold">Do:</span> Get $3k cashback when you refinance to us
  </p>
  <p className="typography-body-10 mb-3 ml-4">
    <span className="text-text-danger font-bold">Don't:</span> Get $3K Cashback When You Refinance To Us
  </p>
</div>
```

*Note: No full stops on the end of any headings - see* [*Headings and subheadings*](/content/guidelines/headings-subheading)*.*
